, France":"Tancarville, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, Frankrijk"},"en":{"1155–1214":"1155–1214","1150–1214":"1150–1214","1180–1215":"1180–1215","1183–1248":"1183–1248","1190–1236":"1190–1236","1190":"1190","about 1170":"about 1170","1248":"1248","1215":"1215","1214":"1214","1236":"1236","1155":"1155","1183":"1183","1150":"1150","1192":"about 1183","1180":"1180","Le Havre, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, França":"Le Havre, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France","Tancarville, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France":"Tancarville, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France","Tancarville, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, France":"Tancarville, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France","Sérans, Orne, Normandy, France":"Sérans, Orne, Normandy, France","Tancarville, Le Havre, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, France":"Tancarville, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"MEULAN","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Galician (<b>Merlán</b>): habitational name from any of the seven places called Merlán in Galicia (Spain), from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Merila</i>.","Romanian: nickname derived from <i>mierlă</i> ‘blackbird’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Aelis","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Alice","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."]},{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Dame Aelis de MEULAN Damme de Tancaeville was born in 1155, in Sérans, Orne, Normandy, France. She married Guillaume III de TANCARVILLE Chamberlain de Normandie about 1170. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. She died in 1214, in Tancarville, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1155–1214":"1155–1214","1150–1214":"1150–1214","1180–1215":"1180–1215","1183–1248":"1183–1248","1190–1236":"1190–1236","1190":"1190","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1248":"1248","1215":"1215","1214":"1214","1236":"1236","1155":"1155","1183":"1183","1150":"1150","1192":"umbes 1183","1180":"1180","Le Havre, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, França":"Le Havre, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Tancarville, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France":"Tancarville, Seine-Maritime, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Tancarville, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, France":"Tancarville, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Sérans, Orne, Normandy, France":"Sérans, Orne, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Tancarville, Le Havre, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, France":"Tancarville, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1155–1214":"1155–1214","1150–1214":"1150–1214","1180